{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_0174p9bwSJHAoyp6xdFatFC9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Alright, I can see:\n\n1. **No cached agents exist** (agent list is empty) - this is a cold start situation\n2. **Available Roles:**\n   - Programmer (3 skills)\n   - Reviewer (2 skills)\n   - Evolver (8 skills)\n   - Evaluator (6 skills)\n   - Agent Creator (6 skills)\n   - Assigner (7 skills)\n   - Architect (2 skills)\n   - Documenter (1 skill)\n\n3. **Available Tradeoffs:**\n   - Careful (prioritizes reliability and correctness)\n   - Fast (prioritizes speed)\n   - Thorough (prioritizes completeness and depth)\n   - Balanced (moderate on all dimensions)\n   - And variants like Creator Unconstrained, Creator Adjacent, Creator Internal, Creator Distant, Assigner Balanced, Evolver Balanced, Evaluator Balanced\n\n**Analysis of the task:**\nThe task is: \"Prove E88 matrix state strictly exceeds E1H vector state\"\n- This is a **mathematical proof task**\n- Requires: Theorem proving, mathematical reasoning, potentially Lean code\n- **Not** a code implementation task in the traditional sense\n- **Not** a review/documentation task\n- This is closest to a **research/analysis/proof task**\n\nLooking at the available roles:\n- **Programmer**: code-writing, testing, debugging - might help but not ideal for pure proofs\n- **Evolver**: 8 skills including analysis capabilities - could work\n- **Architect**: system-design, dependency-analysis - not a great fit\n- **Documenter**: technical-writing - not right\n- **Evaluator**: Could work for validating proofs\n- **Reviewer**: Could help verify proofs\n\nThe task requires someone who can:\n1. Understand the mathematical/architectural concepts (E88 vs E1H)\n2. Write rigorous proofs (likely in Lean)\n\n\n3. Be thorough and careful in reasoning\n\nFor a proof task where correctness is paramount, I should pair either the Evolver (with its broader analytica